  schema:name "The Algebraic Structure of Work: Free Algebras, Ground Terms, and Operational Signatures" ;
  schema:description "How universal algebra formalizes the work taxonomy — operations as signatures, work as term application, work units as ground terms, and the settlement path as substitution closure." ;
